-------
ENTROPY
-------

The entropy contributions are T*S = T*(S(el)+S(vib)+S(rot)+S(trans))
     S(el)   - electronic entropy
     S(vib)  - vibrational entropy
     S(rot)  - rotational entropy
     S(trans)- translational entropy
The entropies will be listed as multiplied by the temperature to get
units of energy

Electronic entropy                ...      0.00000000 Eh      0.00 kcal/mol
Vibrational entropy               ...      0.00493484 Eh      3.10 kcal/mol
Rotational entropy                ...      0.01101572 Eh      6.91 kcal/mol
Translational entropy             ...      0.01924704 Eh     12.08 kcal/mol
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Final entropy term                ...      0.03519760 Eh     22.09 kcal/mol

